    "created_at": "2015-01-21T00:42:36Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-01-21T00:42:36Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "In reading about fixed headers and scrolling, we have to put manual invisible negative-margin, positive padding elements on all anchors (what the @Carreau's link suggests, and roughly every resource I have found on the matter)\n\nThat proposal would also have to be applied to all user elements with IDs. _Every_ element with an ID would need such a spacer, not just our own headers. I do not think that is reasonable.\n\nTo me, this means we made a mistake in switching to a fixed header, and the notebook should go back into a statically positioned div, rather than sitting and floating in the body.\n"
  },
